1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:12,733
<i>We are gathered here today
to witness and celebrate</i>

2
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:14,733
<i> the union of two hearts.</i>

3
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:15,833
<i> Hello, everyone.</i>

4
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:17,767
<i>- We're so sorry.
- Thea?</i>

5
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:18,667
<i> You know her?</i>

6
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,333
<i>Marj, it's nice
to see you again.</i>

7
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,900
<i>Who would've thought your
brother-in-law would end up</i>

8
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,467
<i> being the love of my life?</i>

9
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,033
<i> Now that you've moved on,</i>

10
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:27,267
<i>maybe we can finally forget
what happened between us.</i>

11
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,400
<i> Oh, come on.</i>

12
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,833
<i>Let's not force something
that's already broken.</i>

13
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:32,300
<i> Dad's here.</i>

14
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:36,267
<i>Enjoy the spotlight
while it lasts, Mrs. Torrecampo.</i>

15
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>You didn't even let me walk you
down the aisle.</i>

16
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:41,467
<i> That's enough, Lito!</i>

17
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Enough!</i>

18
00:00:56,233 --> 00:00:57,500
<i> Marj.</i>

19
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:59,767
They're looking for you
at the reception.

20
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:00,933
Do you want some water?

21
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:02,967
Or a makeup touch-up?

22
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:05,900
Thea, can you just leave me
alone for a minute?

23
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,467
I just wanted to check on you.

24
00:01:11,733 --> 00:01:15,600
Even if we're not okay,
I still care.

25
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:18,600
Marj, please.

26
00:01:18,733 --> 00:01:20,600
Don't cry.

27
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,700
You don't deserve this.

28
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,167
And I don't deserve you
messing with my head.

29
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:27,567
Please, just leave me alone.

30
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,367
Marj, no.

31
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:33,767
I just want to help you.

32
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:37,467
What is your problem?
Can you please just back off?

33
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:40,600
<i> Marj! What's going on?</i>

34
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,400
Why are you yelling at Thea?

35
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:46,400
Auntie, I'm sorry.

36
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,867
I was the one
who approached her.

37
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:54,467
I saw she was alone.

38
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,867
She looked really upset.

39
00:01:57,267 --> 00:01:59,267
I tried talking to her

40
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,067
because I really want us
to make peace.

41
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,333
I already apologized earlier,

42
00:02:06,467 --> 00:02:08,933
but maybe she's just
not ready yet.

43
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,133
I just don't want
to stress her out,

44
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:13,267
especially today.

45
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,633
She deserves to be happy.

46
00:02:18,533 --> 00:02:20,167
You're so thoughtful, Thea.

47
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:25,933
At least you know
how to carry yourself.

48
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:30,200
Not all women do, right?

49
00:02:31,267 --> 00:02:35,667
You're sensitive,
well-bred, and kind.

50
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:42,267
Marjorie, next time,
control yourself.

51
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,500
That kind of behavior
doesn't look good in public.

52
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,133
Don't be like your father.

53
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:51,833
That's not how
a Torrecampo acts.

54
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:54,600
So rude.

55
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:57,033
I'm sorry.

56
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,033
Come on, Thea.

57
00:03:02,167 --> 00:03:03,933
I'll introduce you
to the other guests.

58
00:03:04,067 --> 00:03:05,000
Come on. Let's go.

59
00:03:05,133 --> 00:03:06,000
Of course.

60
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:31,033
Sorry, sorry! I'm so sorry!

61
00:03:31,167 --> 00:03:32,400
Miss!

62
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:33,333
Sorry.

63
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:35,500
The ladies' room was full.

64
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,767
Sorry, it was an emergency.

65
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,267
Well, you're lucky
it was just me.

66
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,100
Sorry.

67
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:44,400
I didn't see anything.

68
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:50,300
Though your zipper's still open.

69
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:54,100
I didn't expect to have guests
even in the bathroom.

70
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,500
Relax, Mr. Torrecampo.

71
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,200
I've seen worse sights
at this wedding.

72
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,667
Do you call Edward
"Mr. Torrecampo", too?

73
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:21,400
Just call me Paolo.

74
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:27,400
Okay...

75
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,000
Paolo.

76
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,600
I'll just grab some tissue.

77
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,033
Of course.

78
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,300
I'll see you around.

79
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,433
Yeah.

80
00:06:00,567 --> 00:06:01,400
See you around.

81
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:28,000
So, how are you
after everything?

82
00:06:29,167 --> 00:06:30,367
Crazy night, right?

83
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,800
I've had worse.

84
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,900
But at least this night...

85
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:38,467
ended with you.

86
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:43,767
You really know
how to turn on the charm.

87
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:49,100
By the way...

88
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:52,700
do you think Paolo's okay
after what Marj's dad did?

89
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:57,167
It's like he got a sneak
preview of married life.

90
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:01,700
Wait, why are you suddenly
curious about them?

91
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:03,467
About my brother?

92
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:06,633
Love...

93
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:11,533
Sorry, our wedding
wasn't perfect.

94
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:15,000
Love, don't be sorry.

95
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:19,467
It ended with a bang, didn't it?

96
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,400
Another round?

97
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:24,300
You're unbelievable.

98
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,633
Love...

99
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,900
I wish things could
just stay this happy.

100
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:36,400
It feels like your
mom's resentment toward me

101
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:38,833
just keeps growing.

102
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,233
And then dad made it worse.

103
00:07:44,967 --> 00:07:48,433
What if things blow up
when I move in with you?

104
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,467
Then...

105
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:55,633
we'll build our own world
inside that house.

106
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:56,533
It's huge.

107
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:58,600
Our own space.

108
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:00,833
Our own peace.

109
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:01,933
Even in the middle
of all the chaos.

110
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:04,033
No!

111
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,667
I just mean...

112
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:10,700
I knew it,
I was right about Paolo.

113
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,000
There's nothing
special about him.

114
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:17,833
You, though, are more lovable.

115
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,800
Kinder.

116
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,333
Stronger presence.

117
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,667
Paolo just likes showing off.

118
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:27,700
Always needs a big plan.

119
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,333
Always needs to win.

120
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:35,033
Because he's trying
to catch up to you.

121
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:41,567
That's why I think I'm too much
for Torrecampo Realty.

122
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:43,467
They can't handle me.

123
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,000
It is what it is.

124
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,200
So let Paolo have
Torrecampo Realty.

125
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,067
All of it.

126
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:56,400
Marj, I didn't marry you
because things were easy.

127
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,300
Not because of expectations.

128
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:01,500
I married you

129
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:04,067
because you're the one I want
beside me on days like this.

130
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,567
Good or bad.

131
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:09,900
Ugly or beautiful.

132
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:19,100
We have our whole lives
to make good memories.

133
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,567
Right?

134
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:23,533
Especially now
that we're married.

135
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,400
And I'm not going anywhere.

136
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:29,567
I'm not going anywhere.

137
00:09:31,767 --> 00:09:35,100
No matter who tries
to come between us.

138
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:37,967
Okay?

139
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:43,133
<i>- Just...
- Come on!</i>

140
00:09:43,267 --> 00:09:44,633
It's kind of a waste.

141
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:51,433
Actually, when your mom
introduced me to her friends

142
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:52,967
at Torrecampo Realty,

143
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,267
I was thinking that maybe
I could apply there.

144
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,200
It's good to start
somewhere stable, right?

145
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,433
No, no, no.

146
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,133
That's not a good idea.

147
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,500
I'm building my own website
development company,

148
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:08,300
so I don't have to work there.

149
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:10,933
And now you want to?

150
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:13,667
That place isn't for me.

151
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:16,000
And it's definitely not for you.

152
00:10:17,733 --> 00:10:19,800
Tomorrow, we leave
for our honeymoon.

153
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,767
When we get back,

154
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:25,700
we'll move straight
into the Torrecampo house.

155
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:26,967
With Jobert.

156
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,133
No second-guessing.

157
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:31,900
No more doubts. Okay, Honey?

158
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:32,867
Okay, Love?

159
00:10:41,633 --> 00:10:42,533
Trust me, Marj.

160
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:44,167
We'll be fine.

161
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,567
Hon, I just want to be somewhere

162
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:57,933
I can get to know
your family better.

163
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:03,600
If not there,
then let's go to your house.

164
00:11:04,267 --> 00:11:05,833
Come on.

165
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:08,600
She's been so kind to us.

166
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:11,300
It feels nice
being part of that world.

167
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:28,267
Welcome, Sir, Ma'am!

168
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,700
- Thank you.
- Welcome, Ma'am Marj.

169
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:31,000
Come in, Jobert.

170
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:32,900
You must be Jobert, right?

171
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:35,100
I'm Yolly.

172
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:37,267
I'll be looking after you
here in the mansion.

173
00:11:38,867 --> 00:11:41,167
You don't need
to watch over me.

174
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:42,700
I'm a grown-up now.

175
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:43,400
Well, yes.

176
00:11:43,533 --> 00:11:44,300
You're a big boy already.

177
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:46,133
New friend,
are you okay with that?

178
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:52,967
This place is huge!

179
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,767
It's like a palace!

180
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:57,800
Jobert, careful.

181
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:58,933
<i> You might break something.</i>

182
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:02,167
- So big! So beautiful!
- Oh no, Jobert.

183
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:05,500
Behave yourself!

184
00:12:05,633 --> 00:12:06,533
What?

185
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,900
Behave!

186
00:12:08,033 --> 00:12:09,300
Wow!

187
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,700
Jobert, come on. Stand up.

188
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:11,500
Come here.

189
00:12:11,633 --> 00:12:14,000
- Let's go.
- Let's go, Pong.

190
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,000
Oh dear...

191
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,733
Miss Regina will get mad!

192
00:12:16,867 --> 00:12:18,100
Behave!

193
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:19,167
Welcome home.

194
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,233
Sorry, sorry.

195
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:21,333
How was Japan?

196
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:21,967
Good, Mom.

197
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:27,967
Good morning, Ma'am.

198
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:30,833
Get used to calling her "Mom."

199
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,867
Yeah, no choice now.

200
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,633
Something we all have
to live with.

201
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,433
And of course, your brother...

202
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:43,567
who has special needs.

203
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,867
But don't worry,
we'll keep him comfortable.

204
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,133
As long as he behaves.

205
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:54,400
- Yes.
- Yes, I behave.

206
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:55,500
And Pong.

207
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,467
Pong?

208
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:02,600
Pong.

209
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,100
Oh my God! Get that slimy thing
away from me!

210
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,900
Paolo, please!

211
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:10,400
Jobert!

212
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:11,633
- Please!
- Jobert!

213
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:12,833
- Jobert!
- Put it back!

214
00:13:12,967 --> 00:13:13,633
- Jobert, put it back.
- Keep that slimy thing

215
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:14,933
away from me! Please!

216
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:16,533
- No!
- Gross!

217
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:18,900
Pong is kind.

218
00:13:19,033 --> 00:13:20,733
He gets baths, too, sometimes.

219
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,967
- Okay, okay.
- Pong's kind.

220
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,033
Okay, Pong is kind.

221
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:25,000
- Put it back inside.
- Jobert, put it back.

222
00:13:25,133 --> 00:13:25,900
Come on, now.

223
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:28,100
We'll take it to your room,
okay?

224
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:29,367
Pong can stay there for now.

225
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,067
Later, we'll go for a walk
and bring Pong.

226
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,000
Thank you.

227
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,500
Sorry about that, Mom.

228
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:43,500
Paolo, please.

229
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:48,533
Remind your brother-in-law
that this is not a pet shop.

230
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:49,800
Yes, Mom.

231
00:13:49,933 --> 00:13:51,167
I'm sorry.

232
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,800
And, Marj.

233
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,567
I hope this doesn't
become a habit.

234
00:13:55,667 --> 00:13:57,100
There is order in this home,

235
00:13:57,233 --> 00:13:59,000
and I intend to keep it
that way.

236
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:03,133
Mom, my brother
didn't mean to.

237
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:10,067
And please tell him not to let
that slimy thing roam around.

238
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,633
I don't want anything
crawling on my floors.

239
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:13,733
Please.

240
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:14,800
Yes, Mom.

241
00:14:14,933 --> 00:14:15,900
Sorry.

242
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,533
A few reminders.

243
00:14:20,667 --> 00:14:23,233
No pets in common areas.

244
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:25,900
No shoes in the piano room.

245
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:31,267
And no raised voices,
especially at dinner.

246
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:32,300
Understood?

247
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:35,933
Good.

248
00:14:39,167 --> 00:14:40,100
Marj...

249
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,433
there are so many rules.

250
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:45,167
It's like my school.

251
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:46,933
Quiet, Jobert.

252
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:49,500
Let's behave for now, okay?

253
00:14:52,733 --> 00:14:53,267
Come on.

254
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,267
Let's go to our room.

255
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,300
- Okay.
- Come on.

256
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:57,033
Okay, Paolo.

257
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,167
Okay.

258
00:14:58,300 --> 00:15:00,267
Nice rug.

259
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,900
<i>Come on, let's see what
your room looks like.</i>

260
00:15:15,433 --> 00:15:16,033
Hi, Love.

261
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,733
You're still thinking
about earlier, aren't you?

262
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:34,700
I'm just worried.

263
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:38,633
I know your mom's
a perfectionist.

264
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:43,167
But how is Jobert supposed
to feel at home

265
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,167
if everything he does is wrong?

266
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,433
She just wants things in order.

267
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:51,100
You said it yourself,
she's a perfectionist.

268
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:53,900
But she's open.

269
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,667
Once she gets used to you
and Jobert,

270
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,000
she'll warm up to you.

271
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,533
Love, this isn't just her house.

272
00:16:03,667 --> 00:16:04,900
It's our house.

273
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:06,533
Okay?

274
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:09,133
So we get to set
our own rules, too.

275
00:16:10,867 --> 00:16:12,900
You know I can adjust.

276
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,600
I can follow rules,
if it's needed.

277
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:19,733
But Jobert doesn't know
when he's doing something wrong.

278
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:21,633
He'll just keep getting scolded.

279
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:24,900
Come here.

280
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,067
Don't worry, okay?

281
00:16:28,767 --> 00:16:29,667
I'm here.

282
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:33,533
I'll talk to mom and I'll ask
her to give Jobert some grace.

283
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:34,533
Okay?

284
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:35,633
We'll protect him.

285
00:16:45,633 --> 00:16:47,900
Pong just had a bath.

286
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:49,300
Go straight. Go straight.

287
00:16:50,667 --> 00:16:52,167
You stay here.

288
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,100
There.

289
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:55,500
Slowly.

290
00:16:55,633 --> 00:16:56,267
Come on!

291
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,367
Run over there.

292
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:02,800
Faster!

293
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,633
I'll chase you!

294
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,767
Don't go there.

295
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:14,100
You'll get electrocuted.
Just like before.

296
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,667
You'll start shaking.

297
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:20,600
Jobert!

298
00:17:20,733 --> 00:17:21,767
Oh God! Jobert!

299
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:22,933
What happened?

300
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:25,367
Wait, don't move!

301
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:27,967
Oh my God, careful!

302
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:30,367
Come here, get out of there.

303
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,333
Slowly. Get out of there.

304
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:32,867
<i> Oh my God!</i>

305
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,267
<i> What happened?</i>

306
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,033
Stand up!

307
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:37,867
What did you do?

308
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:46,200
Do you even know what you broke?

309
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:49,900
That was the Torrecampo
family portrait!

310
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:51,933
It was painted
by Marcelo Villaverde.

311
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:54,767
It's one of the most valuable
artworks in this house!

312
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:55,833
What did you do?

313
00:17:55,967 --> 00:17:57,433
You shattered it
because of your carelessness

314
00:17:57,567 --> 00:18:02,000
and because of that slimy little
thing I told you to get rid of!

315
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,300
I'm so sorry.

316
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:05,567
It's not Pong's fault!

317
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:07,433
It's my fault!

318
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:08,433
Shut up!

319
00:18:08,567 --> 00:18:09,433
Enough!

320
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:11,600
I know you're special,

321
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,567
but there are rules
in this house.

322
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:17,033
Here, we take care of the things
that matter!

323
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:20,833
This is not a house for people
without discipline or sense!

324
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:23,500
Hey! Hey!

325
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:25,433
What's going on?

326
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:30,200
<i> I want my sister.</i>

327
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:30,867
Jobert?

328
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:31,833
Jobert?

329
00:18:31,967 --> 00:18:32,967
What happened?

330
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,800
- What happened?
- Your brother

331
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,867
broke the family portrait.

332
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,067
He's only been here a few days,

333
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,400
and this house
is already in chaos!

334
00:18:39,533 --> 00:18:41,633
Mom, please.

335
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:43,533
Don't yell at my brother.

336
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:46,233
It triggers his epilepsy.

337
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:48,233
Your brother has
so many conditions.

338
00:18:50,867 --> 00:18:51,933
It's okay.

339
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:52,800
<i> Hey, hey.</i>

340
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:53,800
<i> What are you doing?</i>

341
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,100
Don't clean that up.

342
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:58,000
Let Jobert clean his own mess.

343
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,533
Jobert could get hurt, Ma'am.

344
00:19:00,667 --> 00:19:01,567
There's broken glass everywhere.

345
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,067
Did I ask for your opinion?

346
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,967
Let him clean up his own mess!

347
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:05,900
Yolly, I'll do it.

348
00:19:06,033 --> 00:19:07,967
- I will.
- No. No. No.

349
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,233
He has to learn.

350
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,300
He's not a guest here.

351
00:19:12,433 --> 00:19:14,733
He's living under our roof.

352
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:16,867
The least he can do
is keep things in order.

353
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,367
So if he makes a mess,
he cleans it up.

354
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,933
There is one system
in this house.

355
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:23,000
No exceptions!

356
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:26,533
Surely he still has
some brain cells left.

357
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:32,867
Marjorie, we are not the ones
adjusting for your brother.

358
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:37,133
If you want us to accept you,
you should adjust.

359
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:40,000
Learn to fit in!

360
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,533
Stop crying.

361
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:49,867
Calm down.

362
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,167
Marj...

363
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:18,567
Where's Paolo?

364
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:23,167
He's with his dad.

365
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,400
They have a meeting.

366
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:28,633
Marj...

367
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:35,900
Why isn't Paolo's mom kind?

368
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,033
Can we go home? Please.

369
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:42,700
But, Jobert, this is our home.

370
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:47,200
I don't want to be here anymore.

371
00:20:48,667 --> 00:20:53,200
Ma'am Regina is always mad
at Pong and me.

372
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:56,333
I get scared
when people are angry.

373
00:20:56,467 --> 00:21:00,100
Mom Regina is just sad because
the family portrait broke.

374
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:02,367
It was important to her.

375
00:21:03,967 --> 00:21:05,767
I don't want to stay here.

376
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:11,167
The house is big,
but the people are sad.

377
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:14,467
And they're always mad
at Pong and me.

378
00:21:16,967 --> 00:21:19,500
They're not mad, Jobert.

379
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:23,300
They're probably just tired.

380
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:27,400
So let's just be patient, okay?

381
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:31,033
Behave for now,
so we don't get scolded.

382
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,967
The house is nice.

383
00:21:35,433 --> 00:21:37,067
It's clean.

384
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,267
It's comfortable.

385
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,200
There's air-conditioning.

386
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:41,733
The food is good.

387
00:21:42,733 --> 00:21:44,967
And there are helpers
who'll watch you

388
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:46,833
while I'm at work.

389
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,267
Okay, Marj.

390
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:58,933
If you're happy
in the big house...

391
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:01,400
then I'm happy, too.

392
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:04,667
But, Marj...

393
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:09,133
Are you happy in the big house?

394
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,700
And with Paolo's mom?

395
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:22,100
I'm happy
because I'm with Paolo.

396
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:25,933
And I'm even happier
because I'm with you.

397
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:29,700
So don't be sad anymore, okay?

398
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:36,667
Look at Pong.

399
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:39,900
Pong's happy.

400
00:22:45,867 --> 00:22:47,767
It's a Marcelo Villaverde
painting.

401
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:51,433
And it was our family portrait.

402
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:52,500
You know my mom.

403
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:54,967
Of course, she'd get mad.

404
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:57,267
I just wish that if she
had a problem with Jobert,

405
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,333
she talked to me instead.

406
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:03,067
I know...

407
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,100
I know.

408
00:23:04,233 --> 00:23:05,267
Okay?

409
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,400
Don't worry, all right?

410
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:08,300
I'll talk to her.

411
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,667
I'm sorry.

412
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:15,633
I don't want to argue
with your mom.

413
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:19,333
But it really hurts.

414
00:23:19,467 --> 00:23:22,400
It feels like we're not allowed
to make mistakes here.

415
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,500
Don't think about it
for now, okay?

416
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:31,267
It's hard to breathe
in this place.

417
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,967
Especially when
you're not around.

418
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:36,533
What about Jobert
when I'm at work?

419
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:43,033
Then let me help you relax,
okay?

420
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,233
Just breathe for a bit.

421
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:46,633
Let's rest.

422
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:54,000
What if Jobert knocks?

423
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,100
He's asleep.

424
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:56,800
Okay?

425
00:23:56,933 --> 00:23:57,733
He won't bother us.

426
00:23:57,867 --> 00:23:58,833
Come on.

427
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:04,867
You're unbelievable.

428
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:05,867
What?

429
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:15,233
Weng, next time,
less butter, okay?

430
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:17,433
Paolo doesn't like
his eggs greasy.

431
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,000
Mom, it's fine.

432
00:24:21,167 --> 00:24:23,300
So, how was your
first night here?

433
00:24:23,433 --> 00:24:24,333
Did you have trouble adjusting?

434
00:24:27,067 --> 00:24:28,000
Yes, Dad.

435
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,700
The house is really big.

436
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:33,867
It'll take time for me
to learn my way around.

437
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,500
Well, you'll get used to it.

438
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:38,367
Especially since,
eventually...

439
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,633
all of this will belong to you
and Paolo.

440
00:24:50,367 --> 00:24:54,433
I want to come with you
to the office.

441
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:57,100
I don't want to stay
in this house.

442
00:24:57,233 --> 00:24:59,233
Jobert, you can't.

443
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:04,267
Yolly will stay with you,
and you have Pong to play with.

444
00:25:05,767 --> 00:25:07,367
Stay here, okay?

445
00:25:09,033 --> 00:25:13,200
So when do we get to hear
the good news?

446
00:25:15,733 --> 00:25:16,967
I want a grandchild already.

447
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:18,367
Preferably a boy.

448
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:22,700
You know, someone has to carry
the family name.

449
00:25:28,233 --> 00:25:30,300
It's too soon, Dad.

450
00:25:30,433 --> 00:25:32,267
Paolo and I are still busy
with work.

451
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,433
<i> You know what?</i>

452
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:39,300
That's exactly what
I was thinking.

453
00:25:39,433 --> 00:25:42,067
Marj, why don't you just
stay here at home?

454
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,500
Don't work anymore.

455
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:45,567
You don't have anything
to worry about.

456
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,667
That way, you can focus
on starting a family.

457
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:50,867
Thank you, Mom.

458
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:54,000
But my career
is important to me.

459
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:56,667
I don't want to give it up
just because I got married.

460
00:25:57,533 --> 00:25:59,000
Your career can wait.

461
00:25:59,133 --> 00:26:00,600
If you want a stable family,

462
00:26:00,733 --> 00:26:02,500
you need to know
your priorities.

463
00:26:05,533 --> 00:26:07,267
But I can do both, Mom.

464
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:11,067
I just don't want all
my hard work to go to waste.

465
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,600
You can't have everything,
my dear.

466
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:17,067
If you want to raise a family,
you need to make sacrifices.

467
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,600
Just like I did.

468
00:26:20,467 --> 00:26:21,867
Oh, yes.

469
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,167
Look how that turned out.

470
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:27,267
You couldn't even keep
this family together.

471
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:30,700
Your spoiled brat
still left you.

472
00:26:31,767 --> 00:26:34,700
After everything you sacrificed
for him,

473
00:26:34,833 --> 00:26:36,100
he still walked away, didn't he?

474
00:26:45,267 --> 00:26:48,367
It's a shame Paolo and Marj
aren't here.

475
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:51,333
At least they're always
on top of things.

476
00:26:51,467 --> 00:26:55,233
Can we do the "Torrecampo boy"
another time? Please?

477
00:26:55,367 --> 00:26:57,067
You fired one of your staff

478
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,467
because he said
you're not getting any?

479
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,533
If your wife
isn't giving it to you,

480
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:05,000
where do you release
all that tension?

481
00:27:05,133 --> 00:27:06,800
I have an idea that might help.

482
00:27:06,933 --> 00:27:08,767
I think you'll actually
like this one,

483
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:10,033
and your mom will, too.

484
00:27:10,167 --> 00:27:11,800
And who exactly is that?

485
00:27:11,933 --> 00:27:13,067
Hi, Paolo!

486
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,367
I also warned you about someone.

487
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:15,533
You didn't listen.

488
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,500
Looks like you need
to keep an eye on Paolo.

489
00:27:17,633 --> 00:27:19,433
If you don't know
how to stand on your own,

490
00:27:19,567 --> 00:27:20,700
you'll get crushed easily.

491
00:27:20,833 --> 00:27:23,000
What Marj doesn't know
won't hurt her.
